8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Galileo AI and Pitch share a solid foundation of core features including Ai Generation, Export Formats. Where Galileo AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Responsive, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Pitch uniquely offers Templates and Drag And Drop and Brand Kit and Collaboration and Animations and Stock Assets and Api Access, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Galileo AI holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Pitch scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Pitch comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Galileo AI begins at $19/mo. Pitch stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Galileo AI requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
