c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Galileo AI is best suited for designers seeking inspiration, product teams, rapid ideation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Pitch, meanwhile, shines for startups, remote teams, collaborative decks, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Galileo AI describes itself as \"AI design tool that generates editable UI designs from text prompts.\" Pitch, established in 2018, positions itself as \"Collaborative presentation platform for modern teams with AI assistance.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pitch** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Galileo AI is a poor choice — far from it. Galileo AI excels in its own right, particularly for designers seeking inspiration and product teams.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent real-time collaboration, go with Pitch. If impressive ai-generated ui quality matters more to you, Galileo AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
